1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,000
You understand?

2
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:02,560
Yeah.

3
00:00:02,840 --> 00:00:03,840
Yeah, that's cool.

4
00:00:03,999 --> 00:00:05,100
Just for a couple of weeks.

5
00:00:05,240 --> 00:00:06,240
I understand.

6
00:00:07,059 --> 00:00:08,160
Maybe a little longer.

7
00:00:08,380 --> 00:00:08,780
Yeah, whatever.

8
00:00:09,080 --> 00:00:10,080
Whatever.

9
00:00:11,190 --> 00:00:14,340
Look, I'll call you next week and we'll
iron out the details.

10
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:14,880
Okay?

11
00:00:15,080 --> 00:00:16,080
Yeah, yeah.

12
00:00:18,030 --> 00:00:19,190
It was great seeing you, son.

13
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:21,720
You too.

14
00:00:22,060 --> 00:00:23,060
Lou.

15
00:00:31,300 --> 00:00:32,300
Yeah, um...

16
00:00:38,129 --> 00:00:39,129
I'm sorry, Will.

17
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:40,400
You know what?

18
00:00:40,420 --> 00:00:41,716
Actually, this works out better for me.

19
00:00:41,740 --> 00:00:43,896
You know, the Slimmies of Summer come to
class wearing next to nothing.

20
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:44,120
You know what I'm saying?

21
00:00:44,121 --> 00:00:45,400
Well, it's alright to be angry.

22
00:00:46,269 --> 00:00:47,440
Hey, why should I be mad?

23
00:00:48,079 --> 00:00:49,919
I'm saying, at least he said goodbye this
time.

24
00:00:50,359 --> 00:00:53,500
I just wish I hadn't wasted my money
buying this stupid present.

25
00:00:56,295 --> 00:00:56,920
I'm sorry.

26
00:00:57,040 --> 00:00:59,460
You know, if there was something
that I could do... Hey, you know what?

27
00:00:59,580 --> 00:01:00,996
You ain't got to do nothing, Uncle Phil.

28
00:01:01,020 --> 00:01:03,220
You know, ain't like I'm still five years
old, you know?

29
00:01:03,335 --> 00:01:05,417
Ain't like I'm going to
be sitting up every night

30
00:01:05,418 --> 00:01:07,240
asking my mom, when's
daddy coming home, you know?

31
00:01:07,380 --> 00:01:08,040
Who needs him?

32
00:01:08,339 --> 00:01:09,941
Hey, he wasn't there to
teach me how to shoot

33
00:01:09,965 --> 00:01:11,100
my first basket, but
I learned, didn't I?

34
00:01:11,219 --> 00:01:13,476
Hey, I got pretty damn good attitude,
didn't I, Uncle Phil?

35
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:15,220
Got through my first day without him,
right?

36
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:16,400
I learned how to drive.

37
00:01:16,580 --> 00:01:17,360
I learned how to shave.

38
00:01:17,560 --> 00:01:18,776
I learned how to fight without him.

39
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:21,520
I had 14 great birthdays without him.

40
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:23,080
He never even sent me a damn card.

41
00:01:23,220 --> 00:01:24,280
To hell with him!

42
00:01:30,239 --> 00:01:32,119
I ain't need him then, and I don't need
him now.

43
00:01:32,380 --> 00:01:33,800
Well, well... Now, you
know what, Uncle Phil?

44
00:01:34,124 --> 00:01:35,884
I'm going to get through college without
him.

45
00:01:36,174 --> 00:01:37,814
I'm going to get a great job without him.

46
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:39,322
I'm going to marry me
a beautiful honey, and

47
00:01:39,323 --> 00:01:40,800
I'm going to have me
a whole bunch of kids.

48
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:42,676
I'm going to be a better father than he
ever was.

49
00:01:42,700 --> 00:01:44,617
And I sure as hell don't need
him for that, because ain't a

50
00:01:44,618 --> 00:01:47,680
damn thing he could ever teach
me about how to love my kids!

51
00:01:55,339 --> 00:01:56,590
How come he don't want me, man?

52
00:01:56,591 --> 00:01:57,831
How come he don't want me, man?

